<br>
For those of you who don't know, our friend Sanluan was the victim of a trade scam.<br>
<br>
He was asked to conduct a transfer for someone, and he agreed.  Sanluan received items which apparently had a value of approximately 10,000pp to hold.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, it appears that he gave these items to someone who CLAIMED to be the proper recipient, but was not.<br>
<br>
In other words, Sanluan was tricked into giving away 10kpp worth of equipment which belonged to someone else...<br>
<br>
The moral of the story is this:-<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> There are liars and cheats who play Everquest, just as there are in real life.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Do not transfer items for someone you do not know.<br>
<br>
If you ask someone to do a transfer for you, make sure that you trust them.  Give the transferer the precise name of the character who will receive the items.<br>
<br>
Be on your guard at all times.  If in doubt, do not transfer the item.  The proper recipient should be willing and able to prove that they are the proper recipient !<br>
<br>
I really feel for Sanluan.  I would feel terrible in the same situation.  I am sorry that he chose to leave the game... it appears that Everquest has been spoiled for him by the greed and selfishness of one person.<br>
<br>
